# Freelance Marketplace API

A production-ready REST API built with Django and Django REST Framework — a backend clone of Upwork/Freelancer.com.

## Tech Stack

- **Python 3.12** / **Django 5.x**
- **Django REST Framework** — API layer
- **djangorestframework-simplejwt** — JWT authentication
- **django-filter** — filtering and search
- **drf-spectacular** — Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
- **django-silk** — query profiling (development only)
- **SQLite** (development) / **PostgreSQL** (production-ready)

---

## Architecture

```
View → Service → Repository → ORM → Database
```

- **View** — handles HTTP, permissions, serialization
- **Service** — business logic, transactions
- **Repository** — database queries
- **ORM** — Django models

---

## Features

- JWT authentication with email verification and attempt limiting
- Role-based access control (Client / Freelancer)
- Full project lifecycle management (Open → In Progress → Completed)
- Bid system with duplicate prevention and price validation
- Race condition protection via `select_for_update` + `transaction.atomic`
- Automatic freelancer rating recalculation after review
- Filtering, search, and pagination for projects
- Swagger UI documentation

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/tolipjonovqudratillo0423/Freelance-Marketplace-App
cd Freelance-Marketplace-App

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

pip install -r requirements.txt

cp .env.example .env  # fill in your credentials

python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver
```

### Environment Variables (.env)

```env
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key
DEBUG=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-app-password
ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME=100
REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME=1
```

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| POST | `/auth/register/` | Register new user | Public |
| POST | `/auth/login/` | Login, get JWT tokens | Public |
| GET | `/auth/send_code/` | Send email verification code | Authenticated |
| POST | `/auth/verify_code/` | Verify email code | Authenticated |

### Projects
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/common/projects/` | List all open projects | Public |
| POST | `/client/projects/create` | Create a project | Client only |
| GET | `/client/projects/all` | Get client's own projects | Client only |
| POST | `/client/projects/complete` | Mark project as completed | Freelancer only |

### Bids
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/freelancer/bid/` | List freelancer's bids | Freelancer only |
| POST | `/freelancer/bid/create` | Place a bid on a project | Freelancer only |
| POST | `/client/bid/accept` | Accept a bid | Client only |

### Reviews
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| POST | `/review/review/` | Get review for a project | Client only |
| POST | `/review/review/create` | Create a review | Client only |

---

## Project Flow

```
1. Client registers → verifies email → creates project (status: OPEN)
2. Freelancer registers → verifies email → places bid on project
3. Client reviews bids → accepts one bid
   → Project status: IN_PROGRESS
   → Other bids: DECLINED
4. Freelancer completes project → Project status: COMPLETED
5. Client leaves review → Freelancer rating recalculated
```

---

## Filtering & Search

`GET /common/projects/?min_price=100&max_price=500&skills=1&search=django`

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `min_price` | float | Projects with min_price >= value |
| `max_price` | float | Projects with max_price <= value |
| `skills` | int | Filter by skill ID |
| `search` | string | Search in title and description |

---

## Documentation

Swagger UI available at:
```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/schema/swagger-ui/
```

---

## Key Implementation Details

- `UniqueConstraint` on Bid prevents duplicate bids at DB level
- `CheckConstraint` on Project ensures `max_price >= min_price`
- `select_for_update()` inside `transaction.atomic` prevents race conditions on bid acceptance
- `update_fields` used on all model saves for minimal DB writes
- Email verification codes expire after 5 minutes with max 6 attempts
- `silk` profiling enabled only in DEBUG mode